# Tretnix project overview

- Read and follow the root `AGENTS.md`.
- Treat project documentation and approved decisions as canonical.
- Inspect relevant code before proposing non-trivial changes.
- Identify root causes instead of applying symptom patches.
- Avoid unrelated edits, speculative cleanup and arbitrary redesigns.
- Preserve intentional client-specific visual identity.
- Do not claim checks passed unless they were executed.
- Do not expose secrets or weaken backend authorization.
- Do not perform destructive database, deployment or DNS actions without explicit approval.
- After changes, review the diff and report files, checks, results and remaining risks.
